From: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos-ls1046a>
Subject: [PATCH] sdk_dpaa: fix soft lockup during probe by reducing PCD FQs and adding cond_resched

The SDK DPAA ethernet driver triggers a soft lockup (26s+) during
dpaa_eth_priv_probe() because the entire probe path runs without
yielding the CPU. The combination of dpa_fq_setup() iterating through
all FQs and dpa_fqs_init() performing QMan hardware operations for
each FQ exceeds the soft lockup threshold.

Fix by:
1. Reducing DPAA_ETH_RX_QUEUES from 128 to 16. Without FMC PCD
   (Policy Classification and Distribution) programming, the extra
   PCD queues are never used. Each port was allocating 128 PCD +
   128 HI_PRIO_PCD = 256 PCD FQs unnecessarily.
2. Adding cond_resched() in dpa_fq_setup() main loop to yield the
   CPU during FQ metadata setup.
3. Adding cond_resched() in dpa_fqs_init() loop to yield between
   qman_create_fq()/qman_init_fq() hardware operations.

Tested on LS1046A Mono Gateway with NR_CPUS=4 and 5 active MACs.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos-ls1046a>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth.h        | 2 +-
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c | 7 +++++++
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth.h b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
@@ -201,7 +201,7 @@ static inline int dpa_xmit(struct dpa_priv_s *priv,
 #define DPAA_ETH_TX_QUEUES	NR_CPUS
 #endif
 
-#define DPAA_ETH_RX_QUEUES	128
+#define DPAA_ETH_RX_QUEUES	16
 #define DPAA_IP_VERSION_4	4
 
 /* Convenience macros for storing/retrieving the skb back-pointers. They must
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c
index 3333333..4444444 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_dpaa/dpaa_eth_common.c
@@ -1166,6 +1166,8 @@ void dpa_fq_setup(struct dpa_priv_s *priv, const struct dpa_fq_cbs_t *fq_cbs,
 	/* Initialize each FQ in the list */
 	list_for_each_entry(fq, &priv->dpa_fq_list, list) {
+		cond_resched();
+
 		switch (fq->fq_type) {
 		case FQ_TYPE_RX_DEFAULT:
 			if (WARN_ON_ONCE(!priv->mac_dev)) continue;
@@ -1432,6 +1434,11 @@ int __cold dpa_fq_init(struct dpa_fq *dpa_fq, bool td_enable)
 int dpa_fqs_init(struct device *dev, struct list_head *list, bool td_enable)
 {
 	struct dpa_fq *dpa_fq;
+	int fq_count = 0;
 
 	list_for_each_entry(dpa_fq, list, list) {
+		if (++fq_count % 32 == 0)
+			cond_resched();
+
 		int _errno = dpa_fq_init(dpa_fq, td_enable);